The '''St. Lucia Amazon''' (also known as the St Lucia Parrot) (''Amazona versicolor'') is a species of [[parrot]] in the [[Psittacidae]] family. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Saint Lucia]] and is the country's national bird.

Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane]] forest. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]]. The species had declined from around 1000 birds in the 1950s to 150 birds in the late 1970s. At that point a conservation program began to save the species, which galvanised popular support to save the species, and by 1990 the species had increased to 350 birds.{{Fact|date=July 2008}} 

